CLASS DESCRIPTIONS:
Product: Product entity with ID, name, category, price, stock, supplier
ProductInventory: Manages products using Vector<Product>
OrderItem: Item in an order with product details and subtotal
Order: Order entity with items, customer, status, date
OrderManager: Manages orders using Vector<Order>
VectorUtils: Generic utility methods for Vector operations
GenericContainer: Wrapper class for Vector<T> with utility methods
VectorComparisonDemo: Compares Vector vs ArrayList performance
InventorySystemMain: Main application with menu interface
ComprehensiveTest: Tests all classes and edge cases
ThreadSafetyDemo: Demonstrates Vector thread safety vs ArrayList

COMPILE & RUN:
Compile: java
Run main: java HW1.InventorySystemMain
Run tests: java HW1.ComprehensiveTest
Run thread demo: java HW1.ThreadSafetyDemo

ASSUMPTIONS:
Product ID is unique identifier
All inputs are valid

CHALLENGES:
Understanding Vector capacity management (trimToSize, ensureCapacity)
Implementing generic methods with bounded types
Debugging thread safety issues with ArrayList

LEARNINGS: VECTORS:
Vector is thread safe (ArrayList doesn't)
Vector has capacity() method (ArrayList doesn't)
Vector grows by doubling when full

LEARNINGS: GENERICS:
<T> allows type-safe code without casting
Generic methods work with any type
Type safety at compile time prevents runtime errors